  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6783 trading just above the GEX flip at 6781 in PIN regime, dealers are currently net long gamma and providing stabilizing flow by selling this bounce toward the massive +37.6B gamma wall at 6790. The wall_break detection combined with the sharp -16.9% GEX decline suggests recent volatility has dealers actively hedging, but the thick positive gamma cushion from 6780-6800 (all 25B+ walls) should contain moves and promote mean reversion. Key level is holding 6781 flip - any break below puts dealers into negative gamma territory where they'd amplify moves lower toward the -13.7B gamma sink at 6770.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect price to get capped near 6790 and grind sideways between 6780-6790 as dealers stabilize the market.",
